criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) provision of a written informed consent by a guardian;

          -  (2) age over 5 years and less than 18 years;

          -  (3) diagnosis of type 1 or type 2 diabetes based on the WHO diagnostic criteria for
             cases.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) eyelid diseases - eyelid entropion, eyelid ectropion, eyelid, ptosis, and
             palpebral dyskinesia;

          -  (2) conjunctival diseases - pterygium and conjunctivitis;

          -  (3) history of ocular surface chemical injury or use of eye drops with moisturizing
             artificial tears;

          -  (4) history of eye surgery within 6 months or history of retinal laser
             photocoagulation;

          -  (5) systemic diseases - Sjogren syndrome, Parkinson's disease, rheumatoid arthritis,
             Grave 's disease, systemic lupus erythematosus, and others.
